  "prompt": "How did Oliver Sykes damaged his voice exactly?",
  "response": "Oliver Sykes, the lead vocalist of the band Bring Me the Horizon, has spoken about experiencing vocal cord damage due to various factors, including his singing style and lifestyle choices. He has noted that his heavy screaming and harsh vocal techniques contributed to strain on his vocal cords. Additionally, he has mentioned issues related to excessive touring, stress, and possibly lifestyle habits such as smoking, which can adversely affect vocal health.\n\nIn interviews, Sykes has discussed how he found himself needing to adjust his vocal technique and approach to singing in order to prevent further damage and to maintain his vocal health. He has sought vocal coaching and undergone training to improve his technique, focusing on more sustainable methods of singing and screaming.\n\nOverall, his vocal issues can be attributed to a combination of physical strain from his performance style and external factors that have impacted his voice over time.",
